\subsection{Spectral parameter of Maass forms on PSL(2,Z[i])}
\begin{definition}\label{mf.maass.picard.eigenvalue}
\uses{mf.bianchi.hyperbolic3space,mf.maass.picard,mf.maass.picard.laplacian}
Each {{KNOWL('mf.maass.picard', 'Maass form')}} is associated to an **eigenvalue** via the eigenvalue equation $(\Delta+\lambda)f(z)=0$ where $\Delta$ is the {{KNOWL('mf.maass.picard.laplacian', 'Laplacian')}}.  It is convenient to introduce the **spectral parameter** $r$ which is also called the eigenvalue.  Only if one speaks about the **true eigenvalue** one refers to $\lambda$, since by convention **eigenvalue** refers to $r$.  In {{KNOWL('mf.bianchi.hyperbolic3space', 'hyperbolic 3-space')}}, the eigenvalue is connected to the true eigenvalue via $\lambda=r^2+1$.

Keywords: #Maass #Picard
\end{definition}


